                <head>No. 16<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The first progress report on <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 107 (<ref
                        target="#d7">Document 7</ref>) was considered by the National Security
                    Council (<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 473; <gloss
                        target="#t_SP1">S/P</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> files, lot
                    62 D 1) at its 91st meeting on May 16 during which Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName> made an oral report on the recent
                    developments connected with the oil nationalization issue. In general the
                    Council concurred with <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName>’s views,
                    but the point was made that the United States “should indeed give vigorous
                    support to the British in reaching an equitable settlement.…” President
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>, who presided at the meeting,
                    then authorized Secretary <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName> to
                    proceed, in connection with the oil nationalization issue in Iran, along the
                    lines he had proposed and which had been discussed by the Council. A summary of
                    the discussion at the Council meeting is attached to a memorandum from <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJS1">Lay</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_ADG1"
                        >Acheson</persName>, dated <pb facs="0071" n="45" xml:id="pg_45"/> May 17,
                    in file 788.00/5–1751. The progress report is in <gloss target="#t_SP1"
                        >S/P</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> files, lot 62 D 1, <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 107 Series.</p>
            </div>
